def display_side_by_side(dfs:list, captions:list):
    """Display tables side by side to save vertical space
    Input:
        dfs: list of pandas.DataFrame
        captions: list of table captions
    """
    output = ""
    combined = dict(zip(captions, dfs))
    for caption, df in combined.items():
        output += df.style.set_table_attributes("style='display:inline'").set_caption(caption)._repr_html_()
        output += "\xa0\xa0\xa0"
    display(HTML(output))

def RCB_DC_plot(data, xvalue, key, label):
    cf.set_config_file(theme='polar',sharing='public',offline=True)
    data.iplot(kind="bar",x = xvalue,
                  subplots=False,
                  sortbars=True,
                  keys = [key],
                  title=label,
                  theme="polar"
                  )

batsman = [];bowler =[]; b_avg= []; runs= []; tm = []
def performance_indexes_batsmen(batsman_list, bowler_list):
    
    for i in batsman_list:
        pi1 = deliveries[(deliveries.batsman == i) & (deliveries.bowler.isin(bowler_list))]
        pi1.player_dismissed.fillna(0, inplace = True)
        pi1['player_dismissed'].loc[pi1['player_dismissed'] != 0] = 1
        for j in pi1.bowler.unique():
            x = pi1[pi1.bowler == j]
            batsman.append(i)
            bowler.append(j)
            y = x.groupby(['match_id'])['player_dismissed'].sum().reset_index(name = "out_count")
            z = x.groupby(['match_id'])['batsman_runs'].sum().reset_index(name = "runs")
            b_avg.append(y.out_count.sum())
            runs.append(z.runs.sum())
            tm.append(y.shape[0])
            
performance_indexes_batsmen(RCB_batsmen, DC_bowlers)

               columns =['batsman','bowler', 'matches_out','total_matches', 'total_runs'])

bowls = []; bats = []; wi = []; bb = []
def performance_index_bowlers(bowlers_list, batsmen_list):
    for i in bowlers_list:
        p = deliveries[(deliveries.bowler == i) & (deliveries.batsman.isin(batsmen_list))]
        p.player_dismissed.fillna(0, inplace  = True)
        p['player_dismissed'].loc[p['player_dismissed'] != 0] = 1
        for j in p.batsman.unique():
            bowls.append(i)
            bats.append(j)
            xy = p[p.batsman == j]
            #print(p[p.batsman == j])
            wi.append(xy.player_dismissed.sum())
            bb.append(xy.batsman_runs.count())
        
performance_index_bowlers(RCB_bowlers, DC_batsmen)

Method to calculate strike rates¶

In [45]:
def strike_rates(DC_RCB_Data, DC_RCB_Data_boundaries):
    for i in DC_RCB_Data.batsman.unique():
        batsman_.append(i)
        balls.append(round(DC_RCB_Data[DC_RCB_Data.batsman == i].balls_faced.mean(),1))
        runs.append(round(DC_RCB_Data[DC_RCB_Data.batsman == i].runs_scored.mean(),1))
        matches.append(len(DC_RCB_Data[DC_RCB_Data.batsman == i].match_id.unique()))
        
        # matches with more than 3 boundaries and atleast 2 4s in those bounadaries
        data_boundaries = DC_RCB_Data_boundaries[DC_RCB_Data_boundaries.batsman ==i]
        boundaries.append(round(data_boundaries.boundaries.mean(),1))
        no_4s.append(round(data_boundaries.no_of_4s.mean(),1))
        boundary3_24s.append(len(data_boundaries[(data_boundaries.boundaries >3) & (data_boundaries.no_of_4s >=2)].match_id.unique()))
        
    strike_rates_data = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(batsman_, matches, boundary3_24s, boundaries, no_4s,balls, runs)), 
               columns =['batsman','matches_played',"boundary_condition(matches)", 'boundaries', 'no_of_4s','balls_faced','runs_scored'])
    strike_rates_data["strike_rate"] = round((strike_rates_data.runs_scored*100/strike_rates_data.balls_faced),1)
    strike_rates_data["boundary_condition%"] = round(((strike_rates_data["boundary_condition(matches)"]/strike_rates_data.matches_played)*100),1)
    return strike_rates_data


# Boundary condition here is >3 boundaries and atleast 2 4s in it

K_Rabada.player_dismissed.fillna(0, inplace = True)
K_Rabada['player_dismissed'].loc[K_Rabada['player_dismissed'] != 0] = 1

def K_Rabada_wickets_data(data_):
    for i in data_.match_id.unique():
        match_num.append(i)
        match_data = data_[data_.match_id == i].reset_index()
        first_wicket = (match_data.player_dismissed.values != 0).argmax()
        wicket_details = match_data[:first_wicket]
        if wicket_details.batsman_runs.count() ==0:
            status.append("no_wicket")
        else:
            status.append("wicket")
        no_of_balls.append(wicket_details.batsman_runs.count())
    first_wicket_details = pd.DataFrame(list(zip(match_num, no_of_balls, status )), 
               columns =["match_id", "no_of_balls", "wicket_status"])

    return first_wicket_details

from bqplot import Pie
from collections import Counter
from bqplot import DateScale, LinearScale, Lines, Axis, Figure
from bqplot import Tooltip

def pie_plot(pie_data,pie_labels, title):
    pie = Pie(sizes=list(pie_data), labels=list(pie_labels),
              stroke="black",
              opacities = [0.8, 0.8],
              radius=80, inner_radius=0,
              sort=True,
              display_values=True, values_format='0.0f',
              label_color="white", font_size="10px", font_weight="bolder"
              )
    fig = Figure(marks=[pie],
             legend_location = "top",
             title=title,
             fig_margin= dict(top=60, bottom=40, left=50, right=20),
             background_style = {"fill":"grey"}
                )
    fig.layout.width="400px"
    fig.layout.height="400px"
    pie.tooltip = Tooltip(fields=['sizes'], labels=["Count"], formats=["0.1f"])
    return fig
